The California Independent System Operator California ISO has declared a warning
for the California grid and may call for rotating outages between noon and
11:59 pm today, [date] due to excess demand for electricity. Rotating
outages will begin if the CAISO reaches a stage 3 emergency, most likely
during peak hours from 6:00 pm to 8:00 pm. These CAISO rotating outages
typically last about an hour. Southern California Edison (SCE) is requesting customers reduce energy use
to help avoid rotating outages. Additional information is available at
www.sce.com/outage or by phone at 800-611-1911. #ReadySBCUSD

SBCUSD OES
August 12 at 9:19 PM ¬∑

Our region is in store for a significant heat wave beginning Friday and affecting areas away from the coast. Heat risk will be high to very high for most of the population, largely driven by cumulative heat stress as a result of the prolonged nature of the heat, as well as a lack of significant overnight cooling. Heat wave conditions are expected to persist for at least 5-6 days across many inland areas, and possibly longer in some locations, with temperatures that will range between 10 and 15 degrees above normal much of the time. #ReadySBCUSD
